{"repo": "spotipy-dev/spotipy", "pull_number": 1232, "instance_id": "spotipy-dev__spotipy-1232", "issue_numbers": [1231], "base_commit": "6787aabe0f301fbb0008c90e67d52bee76ffa98c", "patch": "diff --git a/spotipy/client.py b/spotipy/client.py\nindex 898384dd..e7bd2b2b 100644\n--- a/spotipy/client.py\n+++ b/spotipy/client.py\n@@ -400,7 +400,7 @@ def artists(self, artists):\n         return self._get(\"artists/?ids=\" + \",\".join(tlist))\n \n     def artist_albums(\n-        self, artist_id, album_type=None, include_groups=None, country=None, limit=20, offset=0\n+        self, artist_id, album_type=None, include_groups=None, country=None, limit=10, offset=0\n     ):\n         \"\"\" Get Spotify catalog information about an artist's albums\n \n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Invalid limit for `artist_albums`\n**Describe the bug**\nThe default limit for `artist_albums` is no longer valid.\n\n**Your code**\n```python\nclient = ...\nclient.artist_albums('4s3cCLEcBhVUWLNDFJjRL1')\n```\n\n**Expected behavior**\nShould return albums\n\n**Output**\n```\nHTTP Error for GET to https://api.spotify.com/v1/artists/4s3cCLEcBhVUWLNDFJjRL1/albums with Params: {'include_groups': None, 'country': None, 'limit': 15, 'offset': 0} returned 400 due to Invalid limit\n```\n\n**Environment:**\n - OS: Linux\n - Python version 3.12.3\n - spotipy version 2.26.0\n\n**Additional context**\nFrom my experimentation, 10 is the highest allowed limit. Current default is 20.\n\n", "hints_text": "This is not a bug. Spotify recently changed a lot of endpoints. Read more about it here: https://developer.spotify.com/blog/2026-02-06-update-on-developer-access-and-platform-security\nMy suggestion would be to change the default limit. Calling it without an explicit limit should not result in an invalid limit\n\n", "all_hints_text": "This is not a bug. Spotify recently changed a lot of endpoints. Read more about it here: https://developer.spotify.com/blog/2026-02-06-update-on-developer-access-and-platform-security\nMy suggestion would be to change the default limit. Calling it without an explicit limit should not result in an invalid limit\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/spotipy-dev/spotipy/commit/b401fc67edca0d8ecdd9349ec08f34efd192edc4"], "created_at": "2026-03-11T07:41:18Z"}
